reenFromWeb?topicID=51.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> bug</span><hr size=1> This is an ill-effect or bug with an optimization to reduce network lag several patches ago.<br><br>The theory behind the patch was idle players will not send empty updates over and over again.  There is no need for your PC to get &quot;Joe bob is sitting.. he's still sitting.. yes, still sitting..&quot; 100 times a minute.  So they filter out idle player data to improve lag.  The bug is sometimes the player's model doesnt update from the missing network update, so you have a player that is without a model in the game.<br><br>The player is STILL there, but they need to sit/stand or move to force an update.  <br><br>The other work-around is to simply use the /target command.  Get within range and type /target &lt;playername&gt; and you can now right-click on the empty space and use them like a normal trader.  They are still there, but just updated from their activity.<br><br>Hopefully VI will fix this bug soon, but for now Id rather have a few invisible ghost players than have 300+ players sending &quot;still standing there..&quot; updates in bazaar. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/umoellekajaky.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MoelleKajaky</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/13/02 4:41:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=51.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> AHHHH!!!</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the detailed explanation Owwiefixer! That makes sense...<br><br>Hmm, how they gonn